summary:
The Council:
1. Reaffirms support for the Peace Agreement and Dayton Agreement, calls for strict compliance, and will review implementation.
2. Stresses that authorities in Bosnia and Herzegovina have primary responsibility for implementation, and international community support will depend on their compliance and participation.
3. Reminds parties of their commitment to cooperate with all entities, including the International Tribunal for the Former Yugoslavia.
4. Emphasizes full support for the High Representative's continued role in monitoring implementation and coordinating civilian organizations.
The Security Council:
Reaffirms the role of the High Representative as the final authority in theatre regarding the interpretation of civilian implementation of the Peace Agreement and his power to make binding decisions; 
Expresses support for the declarations of the Ministerial meetings of the Peace Implementation Conference;
Recognizes the authorization to the multinational force to take actions, including the use of necessary force, to ensure compliance with Annex 1-A of the Peace Agreement;
Reaffirms its intention to keep the situation in Bosnia and Herzegovina under close review and consider imposing measures if any party fails to meet its obligations;
Pays tribute to Member States participating in the multinational stabilization force and welcomes their continued deployment;
Notes the support of the parties for the continuation of the multinational stabilization force;
Welcomes NATO's decision to conclude its current SFOR operation and the EU's intention to launch an EU mission;
Authorizes the continuation of the multinational stabilization force (SFOR) for a planned period of 6 months under unified command and control;
Authorizes Member States to take necessary measures to ensure compliance with Annex 1-A and protect SFOR;
Requests authorities in Bosnia and Herzegovina to cooperate with the Commander of SFOR;
Demands respect for the security and freedom of movement of SFOR and other international personnel;
Recalls agreements concerning the status of forces and reminds parties of their obligations;
Requests reporting to the Council through appropriate channels;
Decides on provisional application of status of forces agreements to the proposed EU mission;
Invites States to provide support and facilities for Member States;
Welcomes the EU Police Mission (EUPM) deployment;
